    {
      "id": "5042f712f51d81c7ad4e2691706eaced3892ed63",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 793,
        "name": "Aurelien Degremont",
        "email": "adegremont@nvidia.com",
        "username": "degremoa"
      },
      "date": "2023-04-14 07:53:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nI'm good deleting that. I did not see anybody trying to is for a while and I'm not sure it will bring lot of value as we don't have a clean and stable API. Doxydoc comments are still available through the source and i think this is probably where people are looking at it.\n\nI think it is better to get rid of 'build/' dir which is almost never use and this could be re-added later, in 'doc/' dir or something.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "25e9adcf7dce5b1e114a6fe791834edb501139e5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 931,
        "name": "Timothy Day",
        "email": "timday@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "timday"
      },
      "date": "2023-04-14 18:19:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n> \n> I'm good deleting that. I did not see anybody trying to is for a while and I'm not sure it will bring lot of value as we don't have a clean and stable API. Doxydoc comments are still available through the source and i think this is probably where people are looking at it.\n> \n> I think it is better to get rid of 'build/' dir which is almost never use and this could be re-added later, in 'doc/' dir or something.\n\nThe top-level directory could be a good place to put a Doxyfile, if it got re-added or moved. That's what DAOS does: https://github.com/daos-stack/daos/.\n\nI was going to do another patch after this to try and remove the need for the build/ dir entirely.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "a4e4fadd18d1766c24944d33ccb0907c3a2a075a",
